description: Jessie and Alphonse head underground to infiltrate a group of crazed book sellers who are intent on destroying the internet.
title: Prairie Dog Companion

description: A Riddle Terrorist attacks San Diego on a Saturday, and it's up to Sam to stop him before he destroys the city.
title: Sabbath-tage

description: Trent and Piper go undercover and back to school to figure out who's kidnapping the children of San Diego's elite.
title: 16 Hop Street

description: On the eve of delivering the commencement address at USSD, The President of the Navy has three big problems: He can't speak in public without a river of profanity, a member of NTSF is suspected of being programmed to assassinate him during the speech, and his only protection is a robo-cop.
title: Hawaii Die-O

description: A dolphin serial killer is on the loose and the NTSF don't have any leads until Trent visits the deadliest dolphin serial killer in captivity to get a lead  on this new killer... before Sam and Jessie are it's next victims.
title: Dolphinnegan's Wake

description: An early, sexist-ier NTSF agent from 1963 is called in to fight his old hippie nemesis, recently thawed out and escaped from cryo-jail.
title: Unfrozen Agent Man

description: NTSF teams up with a group of anti terrorism time-travelers from the future here to prevent crimes that haven't happened yet - but will happen in the future.
title: Time Angels

description: A teen heartthrob rides along with Trent and Alphonse on the case of a brutal killer who likes killing Hollywood directors. Kove starts a podcast.
title: Lights, Camera, Assassination

description: The agents of NTSF:SD:SUV trade in their badges and guns for suspenders and flair in order to save the President of the Navy's Chain Restaurant from its violent competitor, Senor Dicks. But will their plan go down in flames?
title: TGI Murder

description: It's time for the biggest annual event in San Diego, and it's up to Trent and the team to stop a terrorist group known as the F.A.N.B.O.Y.Z., who are intent on killing the the comic book authors that have let them down.
title: Comic-Con-Flict

description: Robot S.A.M. is accused of murder and Trent has to go where no human has gone before: Robot Town, San Diego.
title: Robot Town

description: Alphonse is captured while infiltrating the Little Britain section of San Diego so the team must join forces with their British counterparts, STSF:UK:DDB (Socialist Terrorism Task Force: United Kingdom, Double Decker Bus) to rescue their teammate and save San Diego from the Evil Brits.
title: U-KO'ed

description: Trent's nephew harbors a seemingly peaceful extraterrestrial, but the NTSF team knows there's no such thing as a peaceful illegal alien.
title: Extra Terrorist-rial

description: While celebrating Christmas together at Kove's house, the team is attacked by the evil Alaskan Santa Claus.
title: Christmas Activity

description: When Robot S.A.M. is taken prisoner outside of NTSF:SD:SUV:: jurisdiction, the team becomes a viral video film crew in hopes it will help disguise their rescue mission.
title: A Hard Drive to Swallow

description: The Time Angels return and this time the hot time traveling trio protects the future by traveling to the Wild Wild West.
title: The Great Train Stoppery

description: Trent struggles to regain control of a hijacked plane filled with Comic Con convicts, while Kove and Alphonse debate whether or not to remotely blow it up.
title: Comic Con-Air

description: Trent's children learn the true meaning of Christmas when a terrorist dressed as Santa takes over the mall.
title: Wreck the Malls

description: Kove's little black book is stolen by someone from her past and the only NTSF agent talented enough to help her is dead. Or is he?
title: Burn After Killing

description: Before Piper was a sexy superagent, she was an awkward, unpopular college student with a fondness for tight vinyl bodysuits.

input: How Piper Got Her Groove Initially

title: How Piper Got Her Groove Initially

description: The NTSF team shows off their new home security system and free iPhone app.
title: The NTSF:SD:SUV::HISS Infomercial

description: A terrorist has rigged a San Diego bus to explode if it goes over 0mph. It's up to NTSF to keep the bus from moving and figure out who's behind it!
title: Inertia

description: Trent infiltrates the Swedish virtual pedicab bike racing scene to take down a crew of restaurant terrorists.
title: The Real Bicycle Thief

description: For Trent and Sam, swapping faces to foil a terrorist ring is easy. Giving the faces back is hard.
title: Trading Faces

description: When Piper decides to get married, she finds out the hard way that when your ex-fiance is a ninja, he has a hard time letting go.
title: The Return of Dragon Shumway

description: Gary the Killer Whale is murdered and the NTSF team is blamed. Now Trent, Alphonse and Piper must clear their name before they are disavowed.
title: Whack-A-Mole

description: Alphonse travels home to Alaska to find out who murdered his former partner and to make amends with his father, who disowned him for using a cell phone.
title: Wasilla Hills Cop

description: Trent must kill his father, but things aren't as easy as they sound.
title: Family Dies
